<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">The key changes made:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Removed</strong> the coin image load from <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">preload</code> since we're drawing them instead</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Each coin now has a <strong>yellow circle graphic</strong> that follows its physics body every frame in <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">update</code></li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">When a coin is collected, the graphic is <strong>hidden</strong> alongside the physics body</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">The graphics sync to physics positions so they <strong>bounce and fall</strong> correctly with gravity</li>
</ul></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
