ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Great progress so far! Here's a natural learning path based on what you've already built:</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>You've already covered:</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">✅ Physics &amp; gravity</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">✅ Player movement &amp; animations</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">✅ Platforms &amp; collisions</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">✅ Collectibles &amp; score</li>
</ul>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Next steps in order:</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>1. Game Over &amp; Win Condition</strong> ← do this next</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">If player falls off screen → Game Over text</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">If all coins collected → "You Win!"</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Teaches you scene restarts with <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">this.scene.restart()</code></li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>2. Multiple Scenes</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">A menu/start screen before the game</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">A game over screen after</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Teaches <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">this.scene.start('GameScene')</code></li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>3. Tilemaps</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Build levels using <strong>Tiled</strong> (free map editor)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Load real level designs instead of placing platforms by hand</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Biggest upgrade to your workflow</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>4. Enemies</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">A simple enemy that patrols back and forth</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Player dies on touch</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Teaches game logic and AI basics</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>5. Sound &amp; Music</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Background music</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Jump and coin collect sounds</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">this.sound.add()</code></li>
</ul>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>My recommendation:</strong> Start with <strong>Game Over &amp; Win Condition</strong> right now — it's small, satisfying, and directly builds on your current code.</p>
